---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Gemini Automator Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-12">
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-2">Last Updated: December 9, 2025</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy for Gemini Prompt Automator</h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-6">
      The Gemini Prompt Automator extension ("we", "us", or "our") is dedicated to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle your data.
    </p>

    <section class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">1. Data Collection and Usage</h2>
      <p>We do not collect, transmit, store, or sell any personal user data to external servers. All data processed by this extension is stored locally on your device.</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Prompts &amp; Settings:</strong> Your prompt queue and extension settings are stored in your browser's local storage (chrome.storage.local) and are never sent to us.</li>
        <li><strong>Page Interaction:</strong> The extension interacts with the Google Gemini website solely to perform the automation tasks you initiate (typing prompts, clicking buttons, downloading images). It does not read or transmit your chat history beyond the immediate technical needs of the automation.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">2. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>This extension automates interactions with Google Gemini. Your use of Google Gemini is subject to Google's own Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. We are not affiliated with Google.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">3. Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this policy, please contact us via the Chrome Web Store support page.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
